  "id": "algorithm_trix_dmi_001",
  "name": "TRIX-DMI Trend Following Strategy",
  "description": "This algorithm employs a combination of the Triple Exponential Moving Average (TRIX) and the Directional Movement Index (DMI) to identify bullish trends in the market. It generates entry signals based on a bullish crossover of TRIX above its signal line, confirmed by the +DI crossing above the -DI, ensuring strong upward momentum before executing trades.",
  "algorithm_type": "TrendFollowing",
  "prompt": "Create an expert-level TrendFollowing trading algorithm in Python that uses a combination of the Triple Exponential Moving Average (TRIX) with a 15-minute timeframe and the Directional Movement Index (DMI) with a 14-period setting. Define entry signals as a bullish crossover of TRIX above its signal line while the +DI crosses above -DI, confirming upward trend momentum. Include an exit rule when TRIX crosses below its signal line or when the Average True Range (ATR) 14-period rises above 1.5 times its 50-period moving average, indicating increased volatility and potential trend weakening. Implement position sizing dynamically based on the inverse of the 14-period ATR to manage risk. Ensure the algorithm filters entries during sideways markets by checking that the Bollinger Bands Width (20,2) is above its 10-period moving average for sufficient volatility confirmation.",
